International award winning airline, Emirates Airlines has welcomed the latest air travel protocols that will facilitate international travel for United Arab Emirates (UAE) citizens, residents and tourists. The airline added that Dubai will be opened for business and leisure for visitors from 7 July just as they would put in place careful measures to ensure the health and safety of travellers and communities. These protocols for travelling in and out of Dubai airports were announced under the directives of the vice president and prime minister of the UAE and ruler of Dubai, His Highness, Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum and the follow-up of Crown Prince of Dubai and chairman of the Executive Council, His Highness Sheikh Hamdan bin Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum and among others. Recently, Emirates also launched a campaign to tell the world that Dubai is open and ready to welcome international travellers. Commenting, HH Sheikh Ahmed bin Saeed Al Maktoum, Emirates chairman and chief executive said, “I will like to thank HH Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid and HH Sheikh Hamdan bin Mohammed for their latest directives to reopen air travel which showed their vision for Dubai as a world leader in business and tourism.